Error: mnemonic 'cop' does not accept this operand
   ╭─[ tests/golden/fixtures/syntax-int-err/input.k65:2:5 ]
   │
 2 │     cop
   │     ─┬─  
   │      ╰─── missing operand
   │ 
   │ Help: `cop` requires an operand: it accepts an 8-bit immediate (`cop #$NN`)
   │ 
   │ Note: On the W65C816, `cop` is the coprocessor / OS-trap software interrupt: the byte immediately after the opcode is a signature byte that the COP vector handler reads to dispatch the trap. The K816 encoder always requires it (write `cop #$00` if you have nothing meaningful to put there).
───╯

