Error: mnemonic 'brk' does not accept this operand
   ╭─[ tests/golden/fixtures/syntax-int-err/input.k65:4:5 ]
   │
 4 │     brk
   │     ─┬─  
   │      ╰─── missing operand
   │ 
   │ Help: `brk` requires an operand: it accepts an 8-bit immediate (`brk #$NN`)
   │ 
   │ Note: On the W65C816, `brk` is a software interrupt: the byte immediately after the opcode is a signature byte that the BRK vector handler reads via the pushed PC to dispatch traps. The K816 encoder always requires it (write `brk #$00` if you have nothing meaningful to put there).
───╯

